# magic-seed (Cursor wrapper)

This is the Cursor packaging of magic-seed. The full platform-neutral workflow lives in `instructions.md` at the repo root (one directory above `.cursor/rules/` once installed). **Read it before acting on any magic-seed intent.**

---

## When to apply this rule

Cursor activates this rule when the developer's request matches the `description` above. Typical triggers:

- "Initialize magic-seed for this project"
- "Design a feature called <name>"
- "Implement the next issue for <feature>"
- "Validate <feature> for PR"
- "Process PR feedback for <feature>"
- "Capture lessons learned for <feature>"
- "Search the knowledge base for <query>"

If the developer expresses any of these intents — naturally phrased or with explicit wizard names — translate it to the corresponding magic-seed action and follow `instructions.md`.

---

## What this wrapper does

This file exists only to:

1. Provide the YAML frontmatter Cursor's agent uses to recognize when magic-seed is relevant.
2. Point the agent at `instructions.md` for the full workflow logic.

All workflow logic — detection, discovery, profile loading, wizard generation, knowledge-base structure, review gates — lives in `instructions.md`. Do not duplicate it here.
